cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the use of bibliometric techniques in national research assessment exercises, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as bibliometrics is a common tool used in this field. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the evaluation of universities, which has societal implications. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are relevant as bibliometric techniques are often used in these fields to analyze and rank research output. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but could be relevant as the paper discusses the evaluation of research output, which could have security implications.
